Ad Text:
Annual base salary from $122,628 to $136,449 (HEW Level 8), plus 17% superannuation and annual leave loading.
Full time, Fixed Term Contract Until December 2026
Supportive, collaborative team with a hybrid working environment based at Macquarie University, Wallumattagal Campus, North Ryde

About the Role

We are hiring for an enthusiastic Senior Data & Integration Specialist that provides technical leadership and is responsible for the day-to-day management of the University's databases and integration platforms ensuring changes and queries are addressed in accordance with the needs of internal and external customers.

This role sits within our MQ Health Team.

At MQ Health we unite the best clinicians, the most astounding researchers and the most dynamic teachers to lead the development of health and medical education and practice in Australia. MQ Health is Australia's first fully integrated academic health sciences centre under a university's leadership. Founded to advance the tripartite missions of clinical care, learning and research, we are bold and ambitious in our pursuit of patient-centred excellence.

Key Responsibilities

Provide technical leadership and specialist data modelling and technical support of relevant pipeline architectures, database or integration platforms and associated tools and technologies

Lead the design, development, implementation, and operational support of integration solutions, databases, pipelines, and system integrations using industry-standard technologies (e.g., HL7, FHIR, APIs, web services, messaging queues)

Collaborating with IT architects, business analysts, and clinical stakeholders to gather requirements and translate them into technical solutions.

Provide advice to MQ clients and MQ IT leadership in relevant subject matter domains, including identification and evaluation of emerging technologies and trends

Oversee and execute the design, implementation, and operation of IT services, technology systems, and infrastructure in relevant domains, including liaison with internal and external stakeholders, service partners and suppliers, and ensure compliance with relevant MQ and MQ IT standards and processes

Manage and review relevant changes to systems and configuration to ensure compliance with operational requirements for service delivery

Assess and plan for availability, performance, and capacity of services and resources to ensure cost-justifiable business needs and service level expectations are met, and future needs are considered

Lead continuous improvement of relevant operational processes, standards and procedures, and ensure that support documentation is developed and maintained to ensure operational tasks are performed reliably and consistently, and to mitigate the likelihood and severity of service outages

Lead the development of relevant technical capability within the MQ IT service support organisation, including knowledge sharing and coaching

Contribute to project work as subject matter expert, working with project manager to scope, size and complete work assigned to agreed performance targets

Comply with relevant EEO and WHS regulations

About You

Tertiary qualifications in a related field or equivalent knowledge, skills and experience with demonstrated commitment to ongoing professional development.

Knowledge and experience as a subject matter expert in one or more relevant data modelling tools (such as erwin), data pipeline technologies (such as Kubernetes, Apache Airflow, Python, Alteryx, etc.), database platforms (such as Oracle, mySQL, SQLServer, etc.), or application integration and data integration platforms and technologies

Higher order analysis, critical thinking and problem-solving skills applied to the relevant data or integration specialisation and technology platform

Knowledge of core Information Technology functions, structure, policies, systems, processes and procedures

Experience in the relevant technical discipline such as data modelling, data pipeline technologies, database development and management

Providing specialist data and/or integration support in the context of a mature IT service delivery organisation supporting both cloud and hybrid on-premises application configurations.

Highly developed analytical and problem-solving skills including the ability to analyse and interpret requirements and information from numerous sources.

About Us

Macquarie is a university engaged with the real and often complex problems and opportunities that define our lives. Celebrating its 60th year in 2024, it was established as a bold experiment in higher education and designed to break from educational traditions to work in tandem with industry. Institutionally we strive for the extraordinary by challenging convention and embracing different views. Our pioneering culture has encouraged and inspired students, staff and collaborators to break free from conventional thinking, and to actively shape the complex issues that define the future of humanity.

Why work at Macquarie

We rank amongst the top employers in the Australian Workplace Employers Index, having recently earned a five-star rating in the QS World Rankings with the highest rating for employability.

Our prime location, we are walking distance from Macquarie University Metro Station and Macquarie Shopping Centre. Not only are we close, look at our benefits on offer:

17% Superannuation

Subsidised onsite parking options

Flexible working options

Training and professional development

Onsite childcare facilities

Discounted health insurance (Medibank)

Onsite vacation care

Employee Assistance Program

Subsidised membership at the Sport & Aquatic Centre

Onsite GP, imaging & physio clinics

*This position will require pre-employment checks such as criminal record check, working rights check in Australia and qualifications check.

Please note we reserve the right to progress or decline an application as well as close the advertisement prior to the stated closing date.

If you're already part of the Macquarie Group (MQ University, U@MQ, MQ Health, MGSM), you'll need to apply through your employee Workday account. To apply for this job: Login to Workday and go to the Careers App > Find Jobs.

A Place Where You Belong

At Macquarie, we believe diversity makes us stronger, inclusion drives our success, and belonging inspires us to do our best work. We are proud to foster a community where different backgrounds, identities, and experiences are valued, and where our people are empowered to thrive through supportive leadership, shared responsibility, and a deep commitment to genuine care and respect for our community. Find out more about our vision for a truly inclusive workplace in our Diversity, Inclusion and Belonging Framework.

Flexible Work
At Macquarie, we believe by providing flexibility in when, where and how work is done, we can support our staff to manage their personal commitments, while optimising their work performance and contributions to the University. See how we lead in flexible work to enable an outcome focused and inclusive workplace. To learn more about our culture and hiring process, visit our Jobs at Macquarie page.

Data Engineer | 12-Month Contract

Are you a Data Engineer ready to make an impact in a major government organisation?

A fantastic 12-month contract opportunity is available for a highly skilled Data Engineer to join the Business Intelligence and Analytics team at Brisbane City Council. This role is perfect for a self-motivated professional with a passion for delivering solutions that enable data-driven insights.

You will play a critical role in the full project lifecycle, from understanding business needs to developing and implementing robust solutions. Key responsibilities include creating ETL/ELT pipelines using Azure Synapse Analytics, building semantic models and reports with Power BI, and maintaining source code using Azure DevOps. You'll also be a key collaborator within a supportive team environment.

What you'll bring to the table:

Deep Azure Expertise: Over 5 years' experience with Microsoft SQL databases and Azure Synapse Analytics is a must.

Comprehensive Technical Skills: Strong knowledge of SQL, Power BI, and DAX, plus a working knowledge of Python, JSON, and KQL.

Data Warehouse Experience: Proven experience with large, complex Data Warehouses in a cloud-based environment.

Agile Mindset: A strong understanding of Agile delivery methodologies.

This is a chance to apply your expertise on high-impact projects and contribute to the Business Intelligence and Analytics function of one of Australia's largest local government organisations. If you're ready for your next challenge and want to work in a dynamic, forward-thinking environment, we encourage you to apply.

The Data Scientist can be based in either our Brisbane or Parramatta office and is responsible for proposing and prioritising data-driven regulatory solutions, conducting advanced analytics to uncover actionable insights and root causes, deploying predictive models to identify and mitigate high-risk situations, leading the development of new risk models, and ensuring the long-term performance and ethical integrity of all data science solution. 

 

Key responsibilities of this role are:

Develop statistical learning models and custom algorithms.
Collaborate with internal teams and subject matter experts.
Communicate findings to decision-makers.
Document technical and business solutions.
Promote a safe and healthy work environment.

 

Skills & Capabilities

Strong knowledge of statistical and data mining techniques.
Experience with machine learning, predictive modelling, and pattern recognition.
Proficiency in Python, SQL, PySQL, R, and Databricks ML.
Analytical mindset with strong problem-solving skills.
Excellent communication and teamwork abilities.

 

NHVR are currently undertaking growth and considerable transformation, and this is an exciting time to join the organisation.

To be successful in this role you will possess

Essential:

Degree in computer science, statistics, applied mathematics, or equivalent experience.
Experience with Databricks AutoML and Microsoft Azure.

Why join us?

The National Heavy Vehicle Regulator (NHVR) commenced operations in 2013 as the national entity responsible for regulating all vehicles in Australia over 4.5 tonnes gross vehicle mass. The NHVR minimises the compliance burden on the heavy vehicle transport industry, reduces duplication and inconsistences across state and territory borders, and ultimately for the heavy vehicle business with government in Australia.

We are headquartered in Brisbane and employ more than 1000 people across the ACT, New South Wales, Queensland, South Australia, Tasmania and Victoria.

 

We offer

A competitive package based of $132,034.85 per annum + superannuation
Options for monthly or fortnightly rostered day off.
Additional paid leave over Christmas closure.
Hybrid working environment - up to 2 days from home.
Up to15.25% superannuation through a co-contribution scheme
Leave loading 17.5%
Wellbeing programs - discounted fitness through Fitness Passport, Discount health insurance, flu vaccine, financial programs including discounted banking products, finance information sessions.
Salary packaging options including novated lease.
Discounted IT products including Microsoft and free family password security plan.
Ongoing training and professional development support
Professional membership

Specialist Machine Learning Engineer

It starts with YES!   

At Optus, we are fuelled by optimism, unwavering customer focus, and a team of amazing people. And that's where we come in…. "the amazing people" part! We don't sit back and wait for the future to happen, we are out there crafting our own path through new technology, innovation, and investment. We are truly a challenger brand, with challenger spirit.

Step into the thrilling world of AI and ML as a Specialist Machine Learning Engineer, where you'll be at the forefront of innovation, leading cutting-edge projects that shape the future. This role offers a unique opportunity to collaborate with top-tier professionals, push the boundaries of technology, and tackle complex challenges in a dynamic and rapidly evolving landscape. You'll have the chance to design and implement impactful solutions, utilizing the latest tools and techniques in an environment that champions growth, creativity, and staying ahead of industry trends. If you're eager to make a significant impact and be part of something transformative, this is the role for you

Your day in the life as a Specialist Machine Learning Engineer

Prepare and analyse data to align with data science and machine learning objectives, ensuring alignment with user stories
Develop applications using Spark in Scala, Python, or R, while maintaining adherence to best practices
Contribute to the enhancement of our technology stack by designing new AI/ML capabilities
Adhere to AI & ML Chapter Standards, including Test-Driven Development, coding standards, and DevOps code promotion practices
Assist in configuring and building scalable and efficient AI/ML solutions
Work collaboratively with cross-functional teams to integrate machine learning models into broader systems or applications
Participate in code reviews and foster team growth by sharing knowledge and best practices

Experience required

2-3 years of experience in similar type of role or software engineering / development. Ideally within the AI / ML field
Bachelor's degree in Data Science, Computer Science, Engineering, or a related field (completed or in progress)
Strong understanding of data engineering principles and best practices
Experience or a demonstrated passion for machine learning algorithms and frameworks like TensorFlow or PyTorch
Proficient in programming languages such as Scala, Python, and R, with additional knowledge of SQL being advantageous
Exceptional problem-solving abilities paired with a strong analytical mindset
Excellent communication skills, able to engage effectively with both technical and non-technical audiences
A collaborative team player who is eager to learn and contribute to team knowledge.
Familiarity with cloud platforms such as AWS, Google Cloud, or Azure
Understanding and experience with version control systems like Git

The good stuff …

3 days in the office, 2 days remote - with flexible hours to suit! 
Inclusive carer neutral paid Parental Leave of up to 16 weeks.
All Optus employees have access to resources, webinars and support via the ‘Parents at Work portal' 
Own your own growth by accessing an extensive online and facilitator led learning catalogue - even earn a MBA micro-credential via OptusU (University) 
Connect at work through one of our employee-led volunteer groups: Culture Connect, Elevate Women, Disability Network, Express Yourself (LGBTQIA+), United Veterans and Yarn Network 
Vibrant campus life, variety of facilities including restaurants, cafes, gymnasium, GP, and post office

At Optus, we have an ambitious goal to be Australia's most loved everyday brand. Curious about our culture? Go behind the scenes with our people by searching #OptusLife on LinkedIn. 

Intrigued but don't tick every box? We are building our AI capabilities and value diverse perspectives. If you're driven to join us on this journey, apply now - your passion matters more than a perfect match. 

At Optus, we are strengthened by others and that means valuing diversity and saying ‘yes' to embracing individual differences. We are committed to ensuring that our application process provides an equal employment opportunity to all job seekers, including individuals from diverse gender, cultural and linguistic backgrounds, individuals with a disability, individuals identifying as being part of the LGBTQIA+ community, individuals who may have served in the armed forces or who identify as Aboriginal and/or Torres Strait Islander. If you require any adjustments or accessibility support to participate fairly and equitably in the recruitment process, please email AccessibleRecruitment@optus.com.au along with your preferred method of contact and we will be in touch. 

For more information on Diversity, Inclusion & Belonging at Optus, please visit https://www.optus.com.au/about/inclusion-diversity.

Job Title: Snr Data Engineer (Data Modeling, AWS) - Fixed Term Contract
Ad Text:
Snr Data Engineer (Data Modeling, AWS Cloud) - 12 Months Fixed Term Contract


You are passionate about modernising the Human Resources function through strategic and secure management of cloud data products, pipelines and databases

We are undergoing one of Australia's largest digital transformations and establishing an Engineering function within Human Resources.

Together we bring an engineering culture and passion for DevSecOps and GitOps within the cloud




Do work that matters



As a Snr Data Engineer you will be designing, creating and managing the cloud databases and data pipelines that underpin our decoupled cloud architecture and API first approach. You have proven expertise in database design, data ingestion, transformation, data writing, scheduling and query management within a cloud environment.



You will have proven experience and expertise in working with AWS Cloud Infrastructure Engineers, Software/API Developers and Architects to design, develop, deploy and operate data services and solutions that underpin a cloud ecosystem. You will take ownership and accountability of functional and non-functional design and work within a team of Engineers to create innovative solutions that unlock value and modernise technology designs.



You will role model continuous improvement mindset in the team, and in your project interactions, by taking technical ownership of key assets, including roadmaps and technical direction of data services running on our AWS environments.



See yourself in our team



The HR Data Engineering centre of excellence works in an Agile methodology with our Human Resources business to plan, prioritise and deliver simpler, safer and better data products needed to support our business.



You will work within the People Analytics team, which are working on multiple Gen AI and ML use cases, building out the data assets that will support our goals of leading in technology and AI.



To achieve our objectives, you will use you deep understanding of data modelling and data quality and your extensive experience with SQL to access relational databases such as MS Sql Server and Postgres to identify, transform and validate data required for advanced analytics, machine learning and generative AI requirements.



You will use your experience in designing and building reliable and efficient data pipelines preferably using modern cloud services on AWS such as S3, Lambda, Redshift, Glue, etc to process large volumes of data efficiently.



Experience with data centric frameworks such as Spark with programming knowledge in Scala or Python is highly advantageous. As is experience working on Linux with shell and automation frameworks to manage code and infrastructure in a well-structured and reliable manner.



Experience with Workday or payroll systems as a source for data integration is also highly regarded.



We're interested in hearing from people who:


Can design and implement databases for data integration in the enterprise

Can collaborate with business and technical teams in order to design and build critical databases and data pipelines

Can performance tune applications from a database code and design perspective

Can automate data ingestion and transformation processes using scheduling tools.
Monitor and troubleshoot data pipelines to ensure reliability and performance.

Have experience working through performance and scaling through horizontal scaling designs vs database tuning

Can advise business owners on strategic database direction and application solution design




Tech skills



We use a broad range of tools, languages, and frameworks. We don't expect you to know them all but having significant experience and exposure with some of these (or equivalents) will set you up for success in this team.


Experience with designing and implementing new data models, with field mappings and transformation logic from source systems to domain model.

AWS Data products such as AWS Glue and AWS EMR

AWS S3 ingestion, transformation and writing to databases

Proficiency in programming languages like Python, Scala or Java for developing data ingestion and transformation scripts.

Strong knowledge of SQL for writing, optimizing, and debugging queries.

Familiarity with database design, indexing, and normalization principles.
Understanding of data formats (JSON, CSV, XML) and techniques for converting between them. Ability to handle data validation, cleaning, and transformation.

Proficiency in automation tools and scripting (e.g., bash scripting, cron jobs) for scheduling and monitoring data processes.

Experience with version control systems (e.g., Git) for managing code and collaboration.




Working with us:



Whether you're passionate about customer service, driven by data, or called by creativity, a career with CommBank is for you.



Our people bring their diverse backgrounds and unique perspectives to build a respectful, inclusive, and flexible workplace with flexible work locations. One where we're driven by our values, and supported to share ideas, initiatives, and energy. One where making a positive impact for customers, communities and each other is part of our every day.



Here, you'll thrive. You'll be supported when faced with challenges and empowered to tackle new opportunities. We're hiring engineers from across all of Australia and have opened technology hubs in Melbourne and Perth. We really love working here, and we think you will too.



We support our people with the flexibility to balance where work is done with at least half their time each month connecting in office. We also have many other flexible working options available including changing start and finish times, part-time arrangements and job share to name a few. Talk to us about how these arrangements might work in the role you're interested in.



If this sounds like the role for you then we would love to hear from you. Apply today!




Whether you're passionate about customer service, driven by data, or called by creativity, a career here is for you.

Our people bring their diverse backgrounds and unique perspectives to build a respectful, inclusive and flexible workplace. We are working hard to build a team of people who represent the rich diversity of our customers and communities. If you're excited about this opportunity but you don't meet every single requirement, or your experience doesn't align perfectly, we still want to encourage you to apply. You may just be the perfect candidate for this opportunity or another within CommBank.

At CommBank we will inspire you with work that makes a difference, surround you with talented people that respect and value each other, and empower you to grow professionally and personally. Most of all, making a positive impact for customers, communities and each other is part of our every day.

We're determined to make a real difference for Australia's first peoples. We encourage all interested applicants to apply. If you're already part of the Commonwealth Bank Group (including Bankwest), you'll need to apply through Sidekick to submit a valid application. We're keen to support you with the next step in your career.

Job Title: Lead Power Platform Developer - TeamKids HQ
Ad Text:
TeamKids is Australia's highest quality provider of Outside School Hours Care (OSHC), known for delivering fun, safe, and enriching programs that support children, families, and schools nationwide. We're passionate about creating remarkable experiences that inspire lifelong learning and empower communities.

As we continue to grow and innovate, we're looking for a Lead Power Platform Developer to join our Melbourne Head Office and help shape the future of care and education through intelligent, data-driven solutions.


About the Role:

Reporting directly to the Head of Information Technology, this is a hands-on leadership role where you'll be the technical authority on Microsoft Power Platform. You'll lead the design and development of enterprise-grade solutions in a cloud-only environment—architecting scalable applications, automation workflows, and Power BI dashboards, while pioneering AI-driven experiences using Copilot Studio and AI Builder. Working closely with the IT Business Analysts and Project Managers, you'll deliver solutions to drive the business forward.

This role is mission-critical. Your work will directly support TeamKids' purpose by streamlining operations, improving data insights, and enabling smarter, faster decision-making across our national network. From automating enrolment processes to enhancing child safety systems, your solutions will help us deliver genuine impact to families, educators, and communities.
 
Key Responsibilities:

Data Architecture & Integration: Design Dataverse schemas, integrate with Microsoft 365/Azure, and enforce data quality.
App Development: Build Canvas/Model-Driven Apps, Power Automate flows, and custom Apps using .NET and Azure Functions.
Analytics & Reporting: Develop Power BI dashboards and define data governance standards.
 AI & Copilot Development: Create Copilot agents and AI Builder models for intelligent automation and conversational workflows.
Governance & Platform Management: Implement DLP policies, monitor usage, and optimize licensing.
·Leadership & Enablement: Mentor developers, promote reusable components, and drive platform adoption.
What You'll Bring:

Essential:

5+ years in application/platform development, including 3+ years with Power Platform.
Strong expertise in data modelling, Dataverse performance tuning, Microsoft Azure Data Factory, Fabric and cloud integration patterns.
Proven experience building Power BI dashboards and delivering analytics solutions.
Hands-on experience with Copilot Studio and AI Builder for building AI-driven solutions and agents.
Experience with custom app development using .NET, Azure Functions, or similar cloud-native technologies
Deep understanding of Power Platform security, compliance, and governance.
Experience with Power Pages, PCF controls, and Dynamics 365.
Desirable:

Experience with Azure AI/OpenAI services for advanced AI scenarios.
 
KPIs You'll Influence:

% of apps and flows using managed solutions and ALM pipelines.
Reduction in manual processes through automation.
Data quality and performance metrics for Dataverse solutions.
Adoption of Power BI dashboards and analytics across the business.
Deployment and adoption of Copilot agents and AI-driven features.
Delivery of customer applications that extend Power Platform capabilities
Preferred Certifications:

Microsoft Certified: Azure Data Engineer Associate
Microsoft Certified: Fabric Data Engineer Associate
PL-400 (Power Platform Developer)
PL-600 (Solution Architect)
PL-300 (Power BI Data Analyst)
AI-102 (Azure AI Engineer) or equivalent
Why you'll love working with us:  

Hybrid Work Model: Enjoy the flexibility of working from home and the office.  
Me Days & Birthday Leave: Take time for yourself with four extra "Me Days" per year and your birthday off!  
Career Development & Mentoring: We're serious about helping you grow.  
Incredible Culture: Join a values-driven team that truly cares.  
Generous Childcare Discount: 95% off if your child attends a TeamKids service.  
Perks & Discounts: Access savings on health insurance, retail, gyms, and more.


Apply today!  
 
At TeamKids, the safety and well-being of children is our highest priority. As part of our recruitment process, we carry out thorough background checks, reference checks, and screening to ensure all potential employees are committed to safeguarding children and have no history of behaviour that could compromise their safety.  
 
We are proud to be an Equal Employment Opportunity employer, and we are committed to ensuring the safety of all children in our care. This means at TeamKids we are passionate about equality and diversity, we value every individual, we passionately protect and ensure every child's safety and are always seeking to be better and do better than yesterday.

Software Engineer – Generative AI / AWS Bedrock
Work with Bluefin Resources on behalf of a leading technology client

Bluefin Resources is partnering with a forward-thinking technology leader to recruit an experienced Software Engineer with deep expertise in Generative AI, AWS Bedrock, Knowledge Bases, Open Search, and related cloud-native technologies.
This is a unique opportunity to play a pivotal role in shaping the future of AI infrastructure, building innovative features and tools, and helping deliver products and services that transform how industries harness the power of artificial intelligence.
Key Responsibilities
Apply your expertise in Generative AI, AWS Bedrock, LLMs, agents, embeddings, and related frameworks, while mentoring and coaching team members in these emerging technologies.
Collaborate with Product Management and Engineering to identify, design, and deliver end-to-end AI use cases — from ideation and prototyping through to deployment, refinement, and ensuring robust guardrails and quality standards.
Design, build, and optimise backend services using Node.js with TypeScript, ensuring scalability, performance, and security.
Act as a trusted technical advisor to management, stakeholders, and customers, while also providing support and guidance to cross-functional teams.
Take an active role in knowledge sharing, technical chapter meetings, and fostering a culture of innovation within the engineering function.
Keep up-to-date with industry trends in cloud computing, AI/ML, and backend development to continually strengthen the organisation’s technical capabilities.
Requirements
Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or related field.
5+ years of professional software development experience.
3+ years of experience working with Generative AI technologies.
1+ years of hands-on experience with AWS Bedrock and related AI/ML services.
3+ years of Node.js (TypeScript) development experience.
2+ years of experience building and deploying on AWS cloud infrastructure.
Strong problem-solving skills, with the ability to design scalable solutions for complex technical challenges.
Excellent communication skills and the ability to collaborate effectively across diverse teams.
Why Join?
Be at the forefront of cutting-edge AI and cloud innovation.
Work in a highly collaborative environment where your expertise will directly influence product direction and technology strategy.
Partner with a technology leader dedicated to pushing the boundaries of what’s possible with Generative AI.
Bluefin Resources is proud to be supporting this client in the search for outstanding talent. If you are passionate about AI-driven technology and have the skills to make an impact, we’d love to hear from you.

IBM PowerData Integration Engineer

Join a high-impact program supporting secure data integration systems across enterprise networks. We are seeking two experienced IBM PowerData Integration Engineers to support the design, development, and deployment of API-based integration solutions using IBM Power Data Platform technologies. This role will see you engage directly with technical teams and business stakeholders, contributing to critical data infrastructure initiatives.


Location: Canberra or Melbourne

Key Responsibilities:
Engage with stakeholders across business, integration, cyber, and assurance teams.
Design and develop integration solutions using IBM Power Data Platform and approved patterns.
Produce and maintain comprehensive engineering and system design documentation.
Conduct knowledge transfer and training sessions for the Data Engineering team.

Key Selection Criteria:
Proven experience with IBM Power Data Platform and API integration solutions.
Must hold a current NV1 clearance; NV2 and experience in secure environments highly regarded.
Strong documentation and system design skills with attention to detail.
Excellent stakeholder engagement and communication capabilities.

How to Apply

Does this role sound perfect for you? If so, to register your interest in this role, please either contact Brendan Ly or the Compas Team on (02) 6230 0233 and send through your CV by following the link below.


About Compas

Compas Pty Ltd is a Canberra based wholly Australian owned, Recruitment and Services company that has been operating since 1987. We specialise in the provision of permanent, contract and temporary recruitment services, as well as specialised Consulting assignments.


YOUR APPLICATION WILL BE TREATED WITH THE STRICTEST CONFIDENCE

Due to the nature of this environment, candidates must have a current baseline or above clearance.

This role exists to provide data engineering solutions with automated frameworks to the applications on data platform used by the organization to ensure a scalable and reliable solution

Responsibilities

Design, develop and implement complex data solutions to meet business, technical and user requirements.
Lead engineering best practices to uplift capability and delivery quality.
Design and implement data solutions, including data modeling such as Data Vault and different modelling techniques, in close collaboration with the data architect.
Strong and proven hands-on experience in implementing the business use cases using the data-platform (data warehouse and data lake) tool AWS, Talend, Databricks, Spark, Hive and Snowflake and ETL technologies.
Work closely with business and other teams for appropriate design and solution.
Build and optimize data warehouse and data marts ensuring high performance, security and data governance.
Technical ownership for data and data pipelines to ensure compliance with data and architectural standards.
Create and maintain documentation for data pipelines, architectures and processes.

Ad Text:
About us:

At Lockheed Martin Australia, we believe that when people are empowered, inspired, and supported, they can achieve extraordinary things. We embrace flexibility, so our people can be their best inside and outside of work. We champion inclusion and continuous learning, ensuring all voices are heard and valued. And we thrive on collaboration, turning challenges into opportunities for growth and innovation.  As a leader in national security, our innovative and diverse programs create a more secure future for Australia across space, air, land, sea, and cyber domains. Every day is a chance to solve the world’s most complex challenges and make a profound impact. Experience it here.

Responsibilities

The senior cyber architect’s primary responsibilities include:

•        Provide a high level of advice and guidance to a range of stakeholders across the Company with respect to current security measures and recommendations for the implementation of enhancements

•        Provide broad based experience in systems engineering lifecycle & apply experience to specific Cyber Security initiatives relating to architectural design & development

•        Assist with regular cyber testing of systems to ensure continuous security monitoring

•        Support ongoing planning and estimating, status monitoring, measurement and reporting regimes for cyber security activities

•        Develop solutions to a variety of complex problems and provide and implement effective approved solutions

•        Actively attend and contribute to customer meetings as required

•        Actively contribute to the successful completion of specific programs and initiatives

•        Establish and maintain appropriate working relationships, ensuring effective and professional interaction with Lockheed Martin (LM) management, employees, customers, contractors and suppliers

About you:

To be successful in this role you will also have:

·         Significant experience with the systems engineering lifecycle

·         Solid experience in reviewing, interpreting and implementing Information Security Manual or NIST SP 800-53 controls

·         Experience in interpreting security requirements, analysing and recommending security measures and policies Significant experience in risk identification & mitigation practices, including seeking opportunities for continuous business improvement

·         Experience in the evaluation of ICT infrastructure (Hardware/Software) configurations for security vulnerabilities

How we reward and support you:

When you join Lockheed Martin, you work on projects you won’t experience anywhere else.

We offer you a range of benefits built to suit you, no matter what stage of life you are in. 

·         Flexible work & Hybrid work options

·         Access to our online discounts program offering immediate discounts or cashback

·         A variety of leave options including Purchase Leave to support you and your family  

·         Additional benefits such as Novated Leasing and Fitness Programs

·         Learning & Development platforms to encourage ongoing self-development

Special Requirements:

Applicants must be eligible to obtain and maintain an Australian Defence Security Clearance and employment may be contingent on the provision of further personal information including citizenship to ensure compliance with international export control legislation and regulations.

International Traffic in Arms Regulations (ITAR) are applicable and as such, your citizenship (including dual citizenship) may be a factor in determining your suitability for this role.
